# Release Notes for version 1.4

# Noteworthy Changes
- Aggregation: Three methods now available, with additional info in status to display method used more rapidly.
- Shortcut method overhaul: Additional `operations` now fully implemented with bespoke flags in CLI.
- SHEPARD: v1.0 release of automatic padocc job submission (still needs scheduled submission - CRON suggested).
- Validation: Changes to operating methods for comparisons, addition of the AggregationError and ValidationError for fatal dimension issues.

## Bugs
- Fixed a CFA bug with the FillValue attribute (2025.7.18)
- Fixed a CFA bug with dimension attributes affecting the time decoding for Xarray datasets (2025.8.4)
- Fixed duplicated logs bug for projects.

## Changes to preslice method
- Squeezing
- midslice rounding
- get preslice indexing

## Internal mechanisms
- Kerchunk filehandler now uses Xarray-Kerchunk engine instead of fsspec mapper to open the datasets.
- Preslicing in validation now supports squeezing dimensions.
- Switched delimiter for nested reports to ',' (internal-only)
- Switched to using numpy `allclose` from `array_equal` which allows a tolerance in case of datatype changes.
- Support for virtual dimensions added to validation preslicer.

